article.headline: Stringfield leads five in double figures
article.linkText: Vanderbilt cruises in home tournament opener
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) --Cherish Stringfield led five Vanderbilt
women in double figures, scoring 19 points to lead the 
Commodores (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today; No. 14 AP) over Rhode Island 108-53 Friday.

Vanderbilt (3-0) dominated from the start, shooting 64 percent
in the first half to open up a 54-24 halftime lead.

Abi Ramsey added 18 points, Ashley Earley put in 15, Carla
Thomas had 14 and Dee Davis added 12 points and nine assists for
the Commodores.

Vanderbilt was 12-of-18 from long distance, led by Ramsey's five
3-pointers.

Rhode Island (1-2) shot just 34 percent from the floor and was
2-of-11 on 3-pointers. The team was led by Tanya Rhodes' 15 points.
Peta Kneen added 12 points.

Vanderbilt, hosting the annual Thanksgiving Tournament, next
plays the winner of Siena vs. UT-Martin.
